The paper proposes a machine learning pipeline for automated analysis of ciliary motion from videos. This involves identifying regions of cilia, extracting patches of cilia, and classifying patients as exhibiting normal or abnormal ciliary motion. The use of convolutional LSTM networks suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and deep learning (cs.LG). The application of this pipeline to medical diagnosis also suggests a potential fit for artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and bioinformatics (cs.BIO). Finally, the use of videos and motion analysis suggests a possible fit for multimedia (cs.MM).
